        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:12PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 612 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Claryville,
moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
New Richmond, Lindale, Grants Lick, Aspen Grove, Saltair, East Fork
State Park, Mentor, Claryville, California, New Palestine, Gubser
Mill, Nicholsville, Blairsville, Amelia, Ivor, Campbell County Lake,
Alexandria, and Bantam.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
northern Kentucky...and southwestern Ohio.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
